textAnnotations.description:
that, given a zero-indexed matrix A consisting of N rows and M columns of integers, returns the sum
of the elements that belong to the upper spiral of matrix A. The function should return -1 if the sum
does not lie within the range [-100,000,000. 100,000,000]
Assume that:
. N and M are integers within the range [1.1,000,000];
the number of elements in matrix A is within the range [1..99,999,9991;
each element of matrix A is an integer within the range
[-2,147,483,648..2,147,483,647]
For example, given matrix A consisting of 7 rows and 8 columns corresponding to the example
above (i.e. A[0][0] = 5, A[0][1] = 3, A[0][2] 8, A[1][0] = 4, A[2][0] = 4 etc.), the function should return 91
because
5 +3 + 89+41 3(-2)
+ 1 64 +0+ 2
2(-9) 3+3+57
+3+ 1 95
+ 8
+2 3
= 91
Complexity:
expected worst-case time complexity is O(N*M);
expected worst-case space complexity is 0(1)
